The Peugeot family will own about 25
percent of PSA Peugeot Citroen and hold 40 percent of the voting
rights after  General Motors Co. (GM)  buys a 7 percent stake in the
French carmaker, Chairman Thierry Peugeot told  Les Echos .  The family wants to remain the main shareholder of Peugeot
and would not want to drop below 33 percent of the voting
rights, Peugeot said in an interview published in tomorrowâ€™s
